ActExport and Import Permits Act
SubjectOrder Designating the Minister for International Trade as the Minister for the Purposes of the Export and Import Permits Act
PrecisOrder (1) repealing Order in Council P.C. 1983-3832 of December 7, 1983; and (2) designating the MINISTER OF INTERNATIONAL TRADE, a member of the King’s Privy Council for Canada, as the Minister for the purposes of the EXPORT AND IMPORT PERMITS ACT.
